title: Paramilitaries
new-page: true
is-card: true
tags: party_affairs
view-if: reichsbanner_timer <= 0
card-image: img/reichsbanner.jpg
on-arrival: month_actions += 1; reichsbanner_timer += 6
#subtitle: Paramilitary organizing in defense of the republic.

= Reichsbanner

The *Reichsbanner Schwarz-Rot-Gold* is a mass organization for the defense of the Republic against the extremists who threaten it. Some would call it a paramilitary, although currently it is hardly any sort of military. It is officially associated with the pro-democratic parties -the SPD, Center, and [+ ddp_name +], but by far the largest component is with the SPD.

[? if labor_dissent > 60 : The Reichsbanner is having a more difficult time recruiting, as the SPD is no longer the dominant party among the workers. Many of its members have left. ?]

= [? if merger_happened or ddp_name = "DStP": Jungdo ?]

[? if merger_happened or ddp_name = "DStP": The *Jungdo* - national - liberal organization of the VNR and now of DStP. Compared to the other paramilitaries, it's more of semi paramilitary organization with no fireguns or weaponry whatsover. Despite it's non militant nature, Jungdo is quite anti semitic when it comes down to the German Question and membership of Jungdo. ?]

- @militant: Fund more military-style training and equipment for the Reichsbanner.
- @militant_2: Fund more military-style training and equipment for the Reichsbanner.
- @militant_3: Fund more military-style training and equipment for the Reichsbanner.
- @militant_4: Fund more military-style training and equipment for the Reichsbanner.
- @militant_5: Fund more military-style training and equipment for the Reichsbanner.
- @cut_rb: Cut funding for the Reichsbanner.
- @women_rb
- @trans_rb: Allow transgenders to join the organization
- @jungdo: Fund the Jungdo organization with equipment
- @revolution: Launch the revolution across the country.
- @same: Keep the Reichsbanner as it is.
- @easy_discard
- @cancel_advisor_action

#- Orient reichsbanner towards anti-fascism (only available if we have prioritized anti fascism)

@revolution
subtitle: Are we sure? This is irreversible action.
unavailable-subtitle: We do not have enough strength. [? if left_strength <= 50: Entire our party opposes this ordeal as leftists of our party are weak. ?]
view-if: ideology = "left"
choose-if: (rb_strength * rb_militancy > 150) and left_strength > 50

We are going to launch the revolution ourselves. Are you sure?

- @civil_war_1: I am sure.
- @reichsbanner: Let's go back.

@civil_war_1
subtitle: Prepare for it.
on-arrival: kpd_relation += 15; z_relation -= 50; ddp_relation -= 50; dvp_relation -= 80
go-to: civil_war


@jungdo
subtitle: Perhaps, it worth the cost. - 1 resources
view-if: merger_happened
choose-if: ddp_relation > 30 and (merger_happened)
unavailable-subtitle: [? if ddp_relation <= 30: Our relations are too low. ?]
on-arrival: resources -= 1; jungdo_strength += 20; jungdo_militancy += 0.2; ddp_relation += 5; jungdo_training += 1

We have decided to fund Jungdo, our counterpart from the nationalists. Arthur Mahraun is personally thanking us, though this strengthtens nationalists in our allied Democratic / Liberal party.

@militant
view-if: rb_militancy >= 0
choose-if: resources >= 1
unavailable-subtitle: Not enough resources (1) needed.
subtitle: -1 resources
on-arrival: resources -= 1; rb_investment += 1; rb_strength += 100; rb_militancy += 0.02; left_strength += 2; left_dissent -= 2; reformist_dissent += 5; spd_militancy += 0.05; workers_spd += 2*(1-dissent); unemployed_spd += 2*(1-dissent); z_relation -= 5 if historical_mode; ddp_relation -= 3 if historical_mode; z_dissent += 1 if historical_mode; ddp_dissent += 1 if historical_mode

Some in our party decry the increasing militarization of the Reichsbanner. They say it is emulating the right-wing nationalists or the communists, and risks alienating our allies in the centrist parties. On the other hand, more left-leaning radicals are being lured to our organizations, away from the communists.

[? if historical_mode : The Center Party decries the militarization of the Reichsbanner, and its members are leaving the republican organization. Same can be said about Democrats of the DDP. ?]


